name: Paired omics data platform
description: The Paired Omics Data Platform is a community-based initiative standardizing links between genomic and metabolomics data in a computer readable format to further the field of natural products discovery. The goals are to link molecules to their producers, find large scale genome-metabolome associations, use genomic data to assist in structural elucidation of molecules, and provide a centralized database for paired datasets.

name: ONAP DCAE Designtime
description: ONAP-DCAE-Designtime will include components to support microservice onboarding and design. GUI is provided for designer to construct service flow and distribute to DCAE runtime environment
description_good_justification: The description is provided on wiki - https://wiki.onap.org/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=71837460
interact_justification:
The following URLs describe the process to join the community, developing the software and provide feekback: https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Joining+the+Community https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Tracking+Issues+with+JIRA https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Developing+ONAP.
In addition, DCAE has a web page providing DCAE specific information: https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/DCAE+Contribution+and+Development.
contribution_justification:
The process could be found in the following URL: https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Development+Procedures+and+Policies.
In addition, DCAE has a web page providing DCAE specific information: https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/DCAE+Contribution+and+Development.
contribution_requirements_justification:
The process could be found in the following URL: https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Development+Procedures+and+Policies.
In addition, DCAE has a web page providing DCAE specific information: https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/DCAE+Contribution+and+Development.
license_location_justification: https://git.onap.org/dcaegen2/platform/tree/LICENSE.txt
floss_license_justification: The Apache-2.0 license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
documentation_basics_justification: https://docs.onap.org/projects/onap-dcaegen2/en/latest/sections/design-components/index-onboarding.html
documentation_interface_justification: MOD includes Onboarding for external interfacing components. API documentation is available here - https://docs.onap.org/projects/onap-dcaegen2/en/latest/sections/design-components/index-onboarding.html
repo_public_justification: https://git.onap.org/dcaegen2/platform/tree
repo_track_justification: Tracking is provided by using a combination of JIRA and git history. Every commit has an user and a Jira number attached to it.
repo_interim_justification: Gerrit provides an temperate branch for reviewing and providing comments. Once approved, the code will be merged and the temperate branch will be removed.
repo_distributed_justification: Git and and its code review add-on Gerrit are used.
version_unique_justification: Release version is with format ${major}.${minor}.${patch} and will be updated accordingly for each release.
version_tags_justification: Each release is tagged within the Gerrit repository.
release_notes_justification: Release notes include as part of DCAE documentation. For example, R1 release notes can be found at: http://onap.readthedocs.io/en/amsterdam/submodules/dcaegen2.git/docs/sections/release-notes.html#id1
release_notes_vulns_justification: The latest release notes for ONAP projects can be found at: https://docs.onap.org/en/latest/release/releaserepos.html#doc-releaserepos. The known vulnerabilities are reported under the "Known issues" and "Security Issues" sections.
report_tracker_justification: Jira is used to track issues. https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Tracking+Issues+with+JIRA
report_process_justification: The description of the process can be found in the following URL: https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Tracking+Issues+with+JIRA
report_responses_justification: The reported issues are being handled as soon as possible.
enhancement_responses_justification: The reported issues are being handled as soon as possible.
report_archive_justification: All ticket reporting and commenting are available on https://jira.onap.org. The Git/Gerrit system enforces a submission gating function that any code change must include a JIRA Issue ID, which the corresponding JIRA ticket's page links as part of progress report.
vulnerability_report_process_justificati: The process on how to report a vulnerability can be found in https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/ONAP+Vulnerability+Management
vulnerability_report_private_justificati:
The process on how to report a vulnerability can be found in
ONAP Vulnerability Management <https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/ONAP+Vulnerability+Management>.

By default all vulnerability reports are private unless modified by the reporter.
build_justification: Jenkins is used for building all software components (e.g. jar, war, pypi wheel packages) as well as docker images:  https://jenkins.onap.org.
build_common_tools_justification: Maven, pip, are used to build software components (jar, war, wheel, etc).  Docker is used to build software packages (docker container image)
build_floss_tools_justification: Maven and docker are under Apache 2.0.  Pip is licensed under MIT.
test_justification:
Junit (under EPL) for Java and Clojure components.  
Pytest (under MIT) for python projects.  
Rebar3 (under Apache 2) for Erlang code.
Robot Testing Framework (under Apache 2) for docker container level testing.
test_invocation_justification:
Junit tests are invoked from mvn.  Pytest tests are invoked by running pytest from command line.  Rebar3 tests are invoked from command line by running rebarr3.  All are included as part of Jenkin builds.  All are standard testing tools invoked in standard way.
Robot Framework tests are invoked by standard Robot methodology, also triggered by Jenkins build jobs.
https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Continuous+Integration
https://wiki.onap.org/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=4718718
test_most_justification: The combination of Junit/pytest/rebar3, and robot testing framework has the ability to cover all the branches and input fields
test_policy_justification: ONAP uses Robot testing framework for automated integration test.  Passing CSIT test cases is a requirement for passing code freeze mile stone: https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Deliverable+for+Code+Freeze+Milestone+Checklist+Template , under "Integration and Testing".
tests_are_added_justification: CSIT test results available on jenkins build result reporting:  https://jenkins.onap.org/view/CSIT/
tests_documented_added_justification:
This is documented on our wiki on Code Coverage and Static Code Analysis:
https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Code+Coverage+and+Static+Code+Analysis and
https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Creating+a+CSIT+Test
warnings_justification: style check, SONAR reporting, and CLM scanning
warnings_fixed_justification:
MOD submission are reviewed/approved based on verify build report - https://jenkins.onap.org/view/dcaegen2-platform-mod/
This project is also in POC/inbuation phase; as it becomes more mature - more strict enforcment to be added.
warnings_strict_justification:
MOD submission are reviewed/approved based on verify build report - https://jenkins.onap.org/view/dcaegen2-platform-mod/
This project is also in POC/inbuation phase; as it becomes more mature - more strict enforcment to be added.
know_secure_design_justification: At present time, majority of DCAE components are contributed by developers from AT&T.  AT&T developers are generally familiar with secure software development practice and experienced in vulnerability resolution because of their internal practice of using Fortify SCA tool from HP.
know_common_errors_justification: At present time, majority of DCAE components are contributed by developers from AT&T.  AT&T developers are generally familiar with secure software development practice and experienced in vulnerability resolution because of their internal practice of using Fortify code analysis tool from HP.
crypto_call_justification: MOD components  are not sourced as libraries
crypto_password_storage_justification: The DesignUI does not support currently username/authentication
delivery_mitm_justification: HTTPS is used to download all ONAP artifacts, and some are signed by the Linux Foundation.
static_analysis_justification: Sonatype CLM scan is applied for static code and dependency security vulnerability reporting.  Its results are available on https://nexus-iq.wl.linuxfoundation.org/assets/index.html.  Language specific unit testing is mandatory for all ONAP projects.  Results are reported to SONAR server.
static_analysis_common_vulnerabilities_j: Sonatype CLM scan is applied for static code and dependency security vulnerability reporting.  Its results are available on https://nexus-iq.wl.linuxfoundation.org/assets/index.html.  The reports contained details of the vulnerabilities and suggestions of fixes.
static_analysis_often_justification: The CLM scan is triggered by key-word command in the Gerrit review system.  It is applied by PTL and committers after new code changes are merged into the system.
dynamic_analysis_justification: ONAP does not employ dynamic code analysis beyond what SONAR and CLM (Nexus IQ) analysis.  The security subcommittee is undergoing a task identifying suitable dynamic analysis tool but at this time none has been identified.
dynamic_analysis_unsafe_justification: DCAEGEN2 components are implemented in Java, Shell and Python. Not using C or C++.
dynamic_analysis_enable_assertions_justi: ONAP does not employ dynamic code analysis beyond what SONAR and CLM (Nexus IQ) analysis.  The security subcommittee is undergoing a task identifying suitable dynamic analysis tool but at this time none has been identified.
dynamic_analysis_fixed_justification: ONAP does not employ dynamic code analysis beyond what SONAR and CLM (Nexus IQ) analysis.  The security subcommittee is undergoing a task identifying suitable dynamic analysis tool but at this time none has been identified.
test_continuous_integration_justificatio:
For each pull request, the project needs to be built successfully before the Merge option becomes activated. The test will be run automatically during the building process as well. Once build successfully and all tests has past, the Merge option will be activated.

https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Continuous+Integration
https://wiki.onap.org/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=4718718
discussion_justification: A mailing list is used for project related discussion. New users could also check, search the old discussion online at onap-discuss website. More details can be found at: https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Joining+the+Community
no_leaked_credentials_justification:
There are several instances of passwords included in the public repos of DCAE as part of the testing/demo deployment configuration.  
They serve as examples for setting up functional demonstrations, and not intended to limit public access.
english_justification: JIRA is used to track bugs. The whole website is in English. Tracking Issues with: https://jira.onap.org, under DCAEGEN2 board.
hardening_justification: MOD NiFI currently does not use headers like CSP currently.
hardened_site_justification: // X-Content-Type-Options was not set to "nosniff". // One or more of the required security hardening headers is missing.
installation_common_justification:
helm deploy onap
helm undeploy onap
dco_justification: ONAP requires both a Developer Certificate of Origin (DCO), and a Contributor License Agreement (CLA). https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Contribution+Agreements
governance_justification:
The project governance is described at https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Community+Offices+and+Governance

Further information can be found at https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/ONAP+Technical+Community+Document
code_of_conduct_justification: ONAP adheres to the Linux Foundation Code of Conduct, found at https://lfprojects.org/policies/code-of-conduct
roles_responsibilities_justification: The key roles in the project and their responsibilities are described at https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Community+Offices+and+Governance
access_continuity_justification:
ONAP uses the Linux Foundation structure to support all projects, including all keys and passwords. Nothing, including all legal rights, is invested in any single person.
We have multiple committers associated with DCAEGEN2:
https://gerrit.onap.org/r/gitweb?p=dcaegen2.git;a=blob_plain;f=INFO.yaml;hb=refs/heads/master
documentation_roadmap_justification: The MOD roadmap is describer in this wiki - https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/DCAE+MOD
documentation_security_justification: The security design and assurance case can be found at https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/DCAE+Security+Design+&+Assurance (permalink https://wiki.onap.org/x/GokDBg).
documentation_quick_start_justification: Information on setting up ONAP can be found at https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Setting+Up+ONAP
documentation_current_justification:
Documentation is updated with each release at 
https://onap.readthedocs.io/en/latest/submodules/dcaegen2.git/docs/
documentation_achievements_justification:
The DCAE platform badge is visible on the project's readme.io page found at https://onap.readthedocs.io/en/latest/submodules/dcaegen2.git/docs/
The DCAE Designtime badge is added to wiki - https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/DCAE+MOD
accessibility_best_practices_justificati: The UI for MOD is provided by upstream Apache/NiFI project; accessibility is not supported by upstream project
internationalization_justification: The UI for MOD is provided by upstream Apache/NiFI project; internationalization is not supported by upstream project
sites_password_security_justification: The project does not store password in the website, repository or downloads.
maintenance_or_update_justification:
All major releases are tagged in gerrit and the artifacts are stored with the release information on onap.nexus. So we can access all old versions of the artifact. If and when a upgrade requires certain steps to be followed they are being added to the release documents as needed
https://gerrit.onap.org
vulnerability_report_credit_justificatio:
Vulnerabilities can be reported using the link
https://wiki.onap.org/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=6591711
Currently we don't have any vulnerabilities reported, but the wiki page explains on how to report a vulnerability and how to report anonymously if you do not want the credit for it.
coding_standards_enforced_justification: Java code use maven-check-formatter part of build but do not enforce currently.  Python components validation through Black is ongoing.
build_standard_variables_justification: DCAE does not build any native binaries
build_preserve_debug_justification: DCAE does not build any native binaries
build_repeatable_justification: All releases are tagged in gerrit(git), and the builds are controlled using jenkins. By providing the git tag information the same image can be build over and over again with same bit-for-bit result.
installation_standard_variables_justific: helm has no optional destination directories, but does let you direct pods to particular worker nodes
installation_development_quick_justifica:
The ONAP components require only java and maven to begin with for a developer to quickly install and test ONAP.
Even for deployment using OOM and the right amount of resources, we can deploy the full AAI/ONAP suite in less than a day. The steps are documented in
https://onap.readthedocs.io/en/latest/submodules/oom.git/docs/oom_quickstart_guide.html
external_dependencies_justification:
External dependencies are controlled using the pom file, which can be found in the root folder for each of the sub-projects, such as
https://gerrit.onap.org/r/gitweb?p=dcaegen2/configbinding.git;a=tree;h=refs/heads/master;hb=refs/heads/master
dependency_monitoring_justification: NexusIQ sonar scan is run on all the projects on a weekly basis
updateable_reused_components_justificati: External components are maintained through Maven. The user can get a list of all included components using the maven dependency tree and can update or reuse as they see fit
interfaces_current_justification: We avoid depending on deprecated/obsolete functions.
automated_integration_testing_justificat: Automatic test suites are run every time before  merging the code. The code check in cannot pass with out jenkins posting a +1 on the review.
regression_tests_added50_justification: When regressions occur, we add tests for them.
test_statement_coverage80_justification: Current coverage for DCAE MOD components ~75%
test_policy_mandated_justification:
Contributing guide lines for development is recorded in
https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Development+Procedures+and+Policies
implement_secure_design_justification: DCAE Team follows secure design principles and validates them as part of gerrit-reviews.
input_validation_justification:
DCAE MOD provides two external interface currently.
OnboardingAPI : used for onboarding new components into catalog; system does basic schema validation - remaining configuration parameters are expected to be validated by the designer/SE
MOD UI : Current UI based on NIFI does not include validation; new UI is being worked which will include data validation in future release
crypto_algorithm_agility_justification: MOD components uses java which supports these configurable options.
signed_releases_justification: All release artifacts are signed by the Linux Foundation prior to release.
version_tags_signed_justification: All release artifacts are signed by the Linux Foundation prior to release.
copyright_per_file_justification: all source and documentation files are required to have copyright notices
license_per_file_justification: all source and documentation files are required to have license statements
code_review_standards_justification: https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/DCAE+Committer+Guidelines (and pages pointed to by it) explains how a committer is to look at each pull request submitted via Gerritt.
assurance_case_justification: The security design and assurance case can be found at https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/DCAE+Security+Design+&+Assurance (permalink https://wiki.onap.org/x/GokDBg).
